ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_e7ddddbb5933c3a2a3c2e8ca48ec5e20" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_27e56f8c7319e4945749aed7a0280370" parent="aspace_e7ddddbb5933c3a2a3c2e8ca48ec5e20" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_14e8fb1b6887e2c5b64df38c764e43fa" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e1d8ef32b83059a569dc48ce7f636445" parent="aspace_14e8fb1b6887e2c5b64df38c764e43fa" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_de5ad9fefc76e1d51b6c9ae50a50e6b6" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_cd719546545b372ebd65beeb7c9773e4" parent="aspace_de5ad9fefc76e1d51b6c9ae50a50e6b6" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "M